The paper deals with the task of semantic parsing, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for training a system with high precision, which involves reasoning over a set of models, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with data distribution, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound and Data) and cs.DB (Databases).
